mechanic here.

176
00:09:14,149 --> 00:09:19,231
I first heard Ted Price actually coin the term Lombax to describe Ratchet's race.

177
00:09:19,871 --> 00:09:23,932
We also liked the idea of him having a voice, which was very new for mascot characters back

178
00:09:23,972 --> 00:09:27,034
then, so we needed someone for Ratchet to talk to.

179
00:09:29,214 --> 00:09:33,436
So the original design for Clank, we painted him as this childlike C-3PO.

180
00:09:33,456 --> 00:09:37,877
We even experimented with having a child voice with a British accent.

181
00:09:38,710 --> 00:09:40,350
And it just wasn't working.

182
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:42,831
It felt like this kind of weird father-son relationship.

183
00:09:42,931 --> 00:09:45,372
So we decided to put the two on more equal footing

184
00:09:45,712 --> 00:09:48,513
and focus on making it more of a buddy story.

185
00:09:49,473 --> 00:09:51,314
For Clank's particular backstory,

186
00:09:51,374 --> 00:09:53,875
he was written as being this factory defect

187
00:09:54,515 --> 00:09:57,696
who almost got scrapped and was saved from the assembly line.

188
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:01,757
Brian Hastings and Ted imagined the game

189
00:10:01,817 --> 00:10:04,138
as feeling almost like an intergalactic buddy cop story.

190
00:10:04,554 --> 00:10:09,598
the wisecracking alpha would shoot first and ask questions later while the logical sidekick would act as his foil.

191
00:10:09,898 --> 00:10:14,541
It's a dynamic that we've seen a lot in movies, but if you drop into a game full of anthropomorphic characters,

192
00:10:14,821 --> 00:10:15,782
