00:39:59,505 --> 00:39:59,905
Ocelot is coming!

794
00:39:59,925 --> 00:40:00,305
Ocelot is coming!

795
00:40:01,679 --> 00:40:05,024
Alright Quark, you ready to let those stallions out of the stable?

796
00:40:05,965 --> 00:40:07,527
I was born ready.

797
00:40:07,908 --> 00:40:09,470
Aldemar!

798
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:14,497
I believe Dr. Nefarious was clear as to the repercussions of leaving your hull.

799
00:40:15,078 --> 00:40:17,180
The clock is ours.

800
00:40:18,002 --> 00:40:19,163
Whoa, uh, wait.

801
00:40:19,980 --> 00:40:23,162
Who? Dr. Nefarious has no authority here, villain.

802
00:40:23,503 --> 00:40:27,105
In fact, I'm not even entirely convinced he's a real doctor.

803
00:40:27,645 --> 00:40:31,407
So return my sidekick's power before I bring the thunder.

804
00:40:36,230 --> 00:40:38,632
You win again, technology.

805
00:40:43,015 --> 00:40:44,976
So as you can see, our animators had a tremendous amount

806
00:40:45,016 --> 00:40:46,297
of fun with Captain Quark.

807
00:40:46,337 --> 00:40:47,838
And of course we even had Nurse Quark.

808
00:40:47,978 --> 00:40:48,278
I love him.

809
00:40:50,750 --> 00:40:55,714
As we headed towards the end of production for A Crack in Time, Brian and I talked about what to do with Dr. Nefarious.

810
00:40:56,055 --> 00:41:01,720
We were fairly convinced this was going to be our last Ratchet and Clank game, and we wanted to kill him off in spectacular fashion.

811
00:41:01,780 --> 00:41:04,743
Something poetic, and nuanced, and beautifully tragic.

812
00:41:05,524 --> 00:41:09,507
Then we put him on top of a flying saucer and slammed him into his own space station.

813
00:41:10,328 --> 00:41:14,292
We even hired an outside effects house to vaporize the entire level after the crash.

814
00:41:15,182 --> 00:41:18,922
We made this guy super dead, and I remember feeling really sorry for whatever poor writer

815
00:41:18,942 --> 00:41:20,943
would have the task of resurrecting him down the line.

816
00:41:21,723 --> 00:41:25,183
We felt at the time that this was like the perfect send-off for such an iconic villain,

817
00:41:25,203 --> 00:41:28,424
but of course, if you've played other games in the series, you know this came back to

818
00:41:28,464 --> 00:41:28,764
bite me.

819
00:41:29,504 --> 00:41:33,885
I remember how during the first game Ratchet was kind of a sarcastic jerk.

820
00:41:34,305 --> 00:41:37,325
By this time we had evolved him to the point where he could have moments like this.

821
00:41:39,886 --> 00:41:42,646
So, I can't talk you out of this, can I?

822
00:41:43,247 --> 00:41:43,507
Ratchet.

823
00:41:43,930 --> 00:41:47,973
We have been on many adventures, but the clock needs someone to protect it.

824
00:41:48,654 --> 00:41:50,935
It is what I was built for.

825
00:41:50,955 --> 00:42:01,903
Our animators actually spent more time on that one shot than any other shot in our cinematics.

826
00:42:02,343 --> 00:42:05,486
And fans sent me messages saying that this is the first time a Ratchet and Clank game

827
00:42:05,526 --> 00:42:06,206
ever made them cry.

828
00:42:08,048 --> 00:42:11,530
And I hope you all realize that there would be spoilers when you came to this talk.

829
00:42:14,380 --> 00:42:16,340
So, Kraken Time hit all of our franchise DNA.

830
00:42:16,360 --> 00:42:19,241
It was a buddy story with heart, imaginative weapons,

831
00:42:19,441 --> 00:42:22,562
robust space exploration, gadgets, quark, vibrant visuals,

832
00:42:23,162 --> 00:42:24,562
Douglas Adams-inspired humor,

833
00:42:24,882 --> 00:42:26,943
and a great balance of shooting and platforming.

834
00:42:28,743 --> 00:42:29,443
And then some.

835
00:42:29,763 --> 00:42:33,584
It featured many favorite features from past games,

836
00:42:34,624 --> 00:42:35,725
plus some familiar ones.

837
00:42:36,885 --> 00:42:38,125
At TGI, I agree, this was definitely

838
00:42:38,165 --> 00:42:39,405
our favorite game in the series,

839
00:42:39,425 --> 00:42:41,966
and what we consider to be a peak for the franchise.

840
00:42:42,712 --> 00:42:45,194
But unfortunately, we had a hard lesson here,

841
00:42:45,274 --> 00:42:47,075
which is don't get cocky.

842
00:42:47,816 --> 00:42:49,837
So every peak has its valley.

843
00:42:50,878 --> 00:42:53,640
One of the things that was interesting is that a lot of

844
00:42:53,660 --> 00:42:56,081
times long-running series faced franchise fatigue.

845
00:42:56,922 --> 00:43:00,584
We'd ship what we thought was our best game and our last one.

846
00:43:01,885 --> 00:43:04,847
But yet, it had done well enough to warrant some sequels.

847
00:43:04,967 --> 00:43:06,848
And so we knew that there were still people out there who

848
00:43:06,888 --> 00:43:07,869
wanted Ratchet and Clank.

849
00:43:09,162 --> 00:43:12,304
But reviewers who liked the game were raising concerns

850
00:43:12,384 --> 00:43:14,285
that the series was getting a bit long in the tooth.

851
00:43:15,046 --> 00:43:18,948
So this was another time for us to adapt or die.

852
00:43:19,509 --> 00:43:22,551
And the next three years, the series took a number of detours.

853
00:43:24,432 --> 00:43:25,953
What we learned after A Crack in Time was

854
00:43:25,993 --> 00:43:29,495
that friendly family games were moving into other popular genres

855
00:43:29,535 --> 00:43:32,517
like couch co-op with titles like Little Big Planet

856
00:43:33,138 --> 00:43:34,278
and Castle Crashers.

857
00:43:35,051 --> 00:43:40,495
We're also finding that fewer younger players were playing less console games or migrating towards mobile.

858
00:43:42,737 --> 00:43:49,322
So we decided to make a four player co-op game Ratchet and Clank all for one and notice that we have our pal doctor Nefarious in the bottom right.

859
00:43:50,223 --> 00:43:59,110
That's the same guy we smash into a space station. So here's another little bonus tip for you never ring a bell if there's even a slight chance that the publisher might want it on rug.

860
00:43:59,730 --> 00:44:04,514
Because after we ship the crack in time Chad desert and Sean McCabe they pitch this new Ratchet game to Sony.

861
00:44:05,010 --> 00:44:09,274
One key piece of feedback they received was to make Dr. Nefarious a playable character.

862
00:44:09,294 --> 00:44:12,716
I just remember hearing this and my jaw dropped. I was like, we just flew that dude

863
00:44:12,957 --> 00:44:16,660
into a space station and Greg Phillips was like, maybe it was just a flesh wound.

864
00:44:18,461 --> 00:44:22,704
So I had to use the Ratchet and Clank comic to get Nefarious off the saucer before it crashed.

865
00:44:24,386 --> 00:44:27,828
Mayhaps not my most elegant retcon, but I think you got to give me a pass on this one, folks.

866
00:44:30,304 --> 00:44:32,105
So the game had a number of highlights.

867
00:44:32,165 --> 00:44:34,486
It took some of our classic Ratchet gadgets,

868
00:44:34,606 --> 00:44:36,867
like the suck cannon and the swing shot,

869
00:44:37,147 --> 00:44:39,648
and turned them into these really cool co-op devices.

870
00:44:39,668 --> 00:44:41,248
You could actually grab other characters

871
00:44:41,268 --> 00:44:42,689
and throw them off of platforms.

872
00:44:42,709 --> 00:44:44,370
You could have a chain of characters

873
00:44:44,410 --> 00:44:45,910
swinging along on swing shots.

874
00:44:46,731 --> 00:44:49,031
And it was also a very gorgeous looking game.

875
00:44:50,212 --> 00:44:51,032
I also thought it'd be funny

876
00:44:51,052 --> 00:44:52,613
to make Captain Quark President Quark,

877
00:44:52,633 --> 00:44:54,814
because I felt like the idea of a lying, pompous,

878
00:44:54,854 --> 00:44:56,494
blowhard celebrity getting elected president

879
00:44:56,514 --> 00:44:57,155
would be hilarious.

880
00:44:58,612 --> 00:45:00,813
It's a joke that has not aged well.

881
00:45:04,675 --> 00:45:12,419
So, All for One embraced many elements of our franchise DNA, but excluded some, most notably the buddy story and the third-person shooting mechanics.

882
00:45:12,900 --> 00:45:17,182
One criticism we weren't prepared for was the title. Fans just found it too kid-friendly.

883
00:45:17,482 --> 00:45:20,704
For the record, Chad and Sean's original title was Foreplay.

884
00:45:23,606 --> 00:45:27,188
When that one didn't clear, the one that I tried to push through was Multiple Organisms.

885
00:45:32,575 --> 00:45:34,256
And there you go.

886
00:45:34,956 --> 00:45:38,277
I think that may have been the fastest no I ever received from Sony.

887
00:45:38,297 --> 00:45:48,919
Okay, so All for One did succeed financially and there was a lot of love for it, but many fans and critics were also disappointed.

888
00:45:50,640 --> 00:45:54,320
What followed was Full Frontal Assault, which returned to classic gunplay.

889
00:45:54,340 --> 00:45:56,541
It had this tower defense context.

890
00:45:57,286 --> 00:46:00,828
but it lacked this heartfelt buddy story and a feeling of space exploration.

891
00:46:02,209 --> 00:46:05,151
2013's Into the Nexus was more of a return to form,

892
00:46:05,191 --> 00:46:09,094
but felt like a half-step towards the epic adventure that people expected.

893
00:46:11,015 --> 00:46:13,156
So, looking at this graph of the series,

894
00:46:13,517 --> 00:46:17,179
and this isn't like an accurate, like I didn't actually measure out,

895
00:46:17,299 --> 00:46:21,202
but it's not to scale, yes. It's clear that we

896
00:46:21,242 --> 00:46:23,583
hit a bit of a lull with these last three games.

897
00:46:25,550 --> 00:46:27,351
While some of these experimental games had done well,

898
00:46:27,371 --> 00:46:29,492
the reception from fans of drones was mixed.

899
00:46:30,112 --> 00:46:34,213
But that's okay, because what we found

900
00:46:34,253 --> 00:46:36,554
is that you really need to embrace the unknown.

901
00:46:36,894 --> 00:46:39,635
And I realize that there's a bit of a contradiction here

902
00:46:39,655 --> 00:46:41,615
where I'm like saying, well, we adapted or died,

903
00:46:41,995 --> 00:46:44,536
but we also had to embrace our franchise DNA.

904
00:46:45,076 --> 00:46:47,977
And the truth is that it's a tough line to walk.

905
00:46:48,638 --> 00:46:50,158
You have to constantly evolve,

906
00:46:50,178 --> 00:46:51,418
you have to constantly change.

907
00:46:52,468 --> 00:46:54,729
but then you also have to know what's made things great.

908
00:46:54,769 --> 00:46:58,229
And trying to stick that landing is very tricky.

909
00:47:00,110 --> 00:47:04,011
So we realized that to keep our series going,

910
00:47:04,031 --> 00:47:05,571
we had to take these bold steps.

911
00:47:05,591 --> 00:47:07,232
We had to take these experiments

912
00:47:07,732 --> 00:47:09,312
to move it into new directions.

913
00:47:11,693 --> 00:47:13,093
So now around the same time

914
00:47:13,153 --> 00:47:14,554
as we were working on Into the Nexus,

915
00:47:15,014 --> 00:47:17,994
development for Ratchet and Clank the movie had begun.

916
00:47:18,355 --> 00:47:20,835
And for us, this was a sign that we had really hit it big.

917
00:47:21,910 --> 00:47:30,691
Never did I dream that there would be a movie based on this franchise with Paul Giamatti, Sylvester Stallone, Rosario Dawson, and John Goodman.

918
00:47:31,271 --> 00:47:35,792
It was great to know that Ratchet, Clank, and Quirk would be voiced by the original actors though.

919
00:47:37,872 --> 00:47:45,994
And while we had some influence over the film, we knew that we had to do right by the fans and make a great game despite being in the position of making a game based on a movie based on the original game.

920
00:47:46,674 --> 00:47:51,095
The team had the challenges that we never had to face before because after I wrote the original draft of the movie,

921
00:47:51,474 --> 00:47:56,277
It was handed off to writer-director Kevin Munro and Jerry Swallow and the Rainmaker team up in Vancouver.

922
00:47:56,637 --> 00:47:58,779
And from there, things started to change around dramatically.

923
00:47:59,179 --> 00:48:05,082
So we got to experience the thrills of parallel development with an animated movie that was constantly in flux.

924
00:48:08,064 --> 00:48:12,787
Insomniac's North Carolina studio director, Chad Desernes, suggested that the PS4 game,

925
00:48:12,827 --> 00:48:16,689
rather than being called a reboot, that we thought of it as a reimagination.

926
00:48:17,730 --> 00:48:21,172
And the movie was going through numerous rewrites, and we were always playing keep up with the changes.

927
00:48:21,728 --> 00:48:24,789
Sony even wanted us to use some of the movie's cut scenes as game cinematics.

928
00:48:25,309 --> 00:48:29,270
And since the movie's storyline deviated from Insomniac's mythology, this presented a challenge.

929
00:48:29,610 --> 00:48:34,931
How do we make a game that feels like our universe when it's based on a movie that's since departed from its source material?

930
00:48:35,451 --> 00:48:38,691
Our solution was to tell the story through the eyes of an unreliable narrator.

931
00:48:40,372 --> 00:48:42,272
This guy, my favorite character, Captain Quark.

932
00:48:42,872 --> 00:48:45,273
Here he is getting the full spa treatment over in Zora Dune prison.

933
00:48:46,813 --> 00:48:50,393
With this device, we can have Quark exaggerate, we can have him lie, we can have him manipulate events.

934
00:48:51,298 --> 00:48:53,739
so we could divert from the movie where we felt it was necessary.

935
00:48:55,701 --> 00:48:59,003
So we updated all of our shooting mechanics and RPG gameplay.

936
00:48:59,043 --> 00:49:01,565
I actually went back and tried to play the original Ratchet & Clank

937
00:49:01,605 --> 00:49:03,647
and all the controls were so weird to me.

938
00:49:03,667 --> 00:49:05,628
I had trouble just shooting something.

939
00:49:06,449 --> 00:49:09,331
So we took all the lessons that we had learned over the entire series

940
00:49:09,871 --> 00:49:13,374
and we improved the game and brought it up to date.

941
00:49:15,155 --> 00:49:17,276
Metropolis made a return visit to this game.

942
00:49:18,646 --> 00:49:22,108
where Ratchet could fly his ship in a city with an insane amount of detail.

943
00:49:24,369 --> 00:49:28,751
So ultimately, revisiting our original game helped us re-embrace what made the series

944
00:49:28,791 --> 00:49:34,354
great, a robot and furry alien from opposite sides of the galaxy who team up to stop a

945
00:49:34,374 --> 00:49:36,415
supervillain and become friends in the process.

946
00:49:36,875 --> 00:49:40,517
We had this wonderful opportunity to have this epic do-over.

947
00:49:41,097 --> 00:49:44,298
We took everything we used about what made Ratchet and Clank.

948
00:49:44,767 --> 00:49:48,709
the world that the characters inhabited and how to face challenges optimistically and

949
00:49:48,749 --> 00:49:51,652
at times fire our engines into the unknown.

950
00:49:54,794 --> 00:49:57,016
